<h2 id="20">2. Displaying own bank details in the online store</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The category <strong>Bank details</strong> is used for displaying your bank details in the online store. A customer requires your bank details when paying with the payment method cash in advance, for example. The bank details will be displayed during the order process when the customer selects the payment method cash in advance or invoice. The information will also be displayed in the <strong>order history</strong> once the order has been completed. The category <strong>Bank details</strong> can contain information about several bank accounts in different countries.</p>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="30">2.1. Customising the Bank details category</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Proceed as follows to customise the <strong>Bank details</strong> category.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Customising the category:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Item » Categories</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the design’s folder, e.g. the folder for Callisto Light 3.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the category <strong>Bank details</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Description 1</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Make adjustments to the description.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>For further information about the settings of categories, refer to the <a href="/en/item/managing-categories#2">Editing categories</a> chapter.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="40">2.2. Displaying bank details in order process</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Below you will find a description of how to save the category <strong>bank details</strong> for the payment method cash in advance. The link is set up the same way for the payment method invoice.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Saving the category for the payment method:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>System » Orders » Payment » Methods</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Place a check mark next to the setting <strong>Also show inactive</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the folder <strong>International</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the payment method.<br>
→ The <strong>Settings</strong> tab will open.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select <strong>Info page (internal)</strong> from the <strong>Info page</strong> drop-down list.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Edit</strong> next to the option <strong>Info page (internal)</strong>.<br>
→ The window <strong>Select item template</strong> will open.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select the category <strong>Bank details</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>Select</strong>.<br>
→ The info page is linked to the payment method.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Place a check mark next to the option <strong>Active</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on the <strong>Interface</strong> tab.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Expand the client.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Activate the options <strong>Show bank details</strong> and <strong>Show designated use</strong>.<br>
→ The customer will see a link to the information if he or she selects the payment method Cash in advance during the order process.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
